summary:
Atypical, passionate Archeology student with a French-German Bicultural profile and international studies in Anglo-Saxon countries (New Zealand and the Netherlands).

Born in Germany, I grew up in France in an international environment and was lucky to do my first trekking in the Sahara desert aged 7, followed by many other adventure travels over 3 continents, which fueled my passion for exploring and understanding Foreign Civilisations and Cultures.

This profound interest in the History of Mankind, as a way to better understand and protect it in the future, has been the backbone of my academic path.

I strive to look for any opportunity to bring my openmindedness, curiosity, patience, quiet determination, languages, and good people-listening skills to the service of International Archeological Project teams in the Middle & Near East, as well as underwater excavations which I aim to specialize in.
